OL,3,CNetwork Rail fined #3.41m over track
OL,4,Cworker death
OL,6,FNetwork Rail has been fined #3.41
OL,7,Fmillion over the death of a track
OL,8,Fworker from Hampshire.
OL,10,FRegulator the Office of Rail and Road
OL,11,F(ORR) said the Government-owned
OL,12,Fcompany was handed the punishment in a
OL,13,Fhearing at Kingston Crown Court, south-
OL,14,Fwest London on Thursday.
OL,16,FTyler Byrne, 30, from Aldershot, was
OL,17,Fworking on tracks for Network Rail in
OL,18,FSurbiton in February 2021 when he was
OL,19,Fstruck and killed by a train
OL,20,Ftravelling at around 76mph.
