OL,6,FThe ORR, which launched the
OL,7,Fprosecution, said Network Rail pleaded
OL,8,Fguilty to an offence under workplace
OL,9,Fhealth and safety legislation.
OL,11,FMr Byrne was part of a four-person
OL,12,Fgroup of track workers carrying out
OL,13,Finspections while trains were running
OL,14,Fin both directions.
OL,16,FThe OOR said the group was exposed to
OL,17,Fthe risk of being hit by a train as
OL,18,Fthere were inadequate warnings and no
OL,19,Fprotection.
